	<h1>About Me</h1>
	<p>I am 28 years old and I have been producing art and working with code for many years. I have a degree from Texas State University in Digital Photographic Imaging (with <a href="http://barrystone.com/">Barry Stone</a>). At Texas State I took a printmaking class with <a href="http://jeffreydell.com/">Jeff Dell</a>, and that got me into my current work of producing Risograph (a risograph is essentially an automatic screenprinter, it looks like a xerox machine) printed comics with my friends. My personal style of illustration involves a lot of photo references, it is true, but I think that I add a large dose of my own personal flair to the subject matter. Although I have done plenty of gallery work and installations, I prefer Risograph printed work as it easy to disseminate. <a href="#cont">(continued below)</a></p>
