	<h2 id="cont">About Me (cont.)</h2>   
    <p>I am the official printer for <a href="http://www.roughhousecomics.com">Rough House comics</a> and <a href="http://www.rawpawatx.com">Raw Paw</a> and that means that I process all the material that goes into the printer as well as actually print it myself. Although this does make me a little money, I am truly interested in getting into the web development game, as a career. I have technically been writing code since I was a kid, working on the old hacked copies of RPG Maker 2000 (check out <a href="http://rpgmaker2000.narod.ru/">this rowdy website</a>, you can still get it), as well as producing my own handmade fan websites for the anime shows I liked (actually the main show I made a website for I never watched, but only read descriptions of the episodes!!). In any case, I went on hiatus from that kind of work to pursue my art degree, which helped me not at all in the art of making money, but taught me valuable lessons about colors and stuff. Head on over to the <%= link_to "coding section", coding_path %> to see what I am up to with that.</p> 
